About The Ottawa Hospital 




      Inspired by research and driven by compassion!




       The Ottawa Hospital (TOH) is one of Canada’s largest learning and research multi-campus hospitals. With more than 1,100 beds and approximately 12,000 staff members, we deliver specialized care to the Eastern Ontario region. 




      From the compassion of our people to the relentless pursuit of new discoveries, The Ottawa Hospital never stops seeking solutions to the most complex health-care challenges while continually engaging with the community to support our vision for better patient care.




       Working together with its research institute, the University of Ottawa, and other partners, the hospital is continually gaining national and international recognition for high-quality patient care, teaching and research, while striving to meet the needs of the culturally diverse community we serve.







   Position Information 




      This position will be located on the E5 Unit.







   Rotation/Shifts 




      Days and nights, including weekends, 12 hour shifts. 


      For information purposes only - The Hospital reserves the right to change.







   Basic Requirements 






        Certificate of registration from the College of Nurses of Ontario;



        Minimum of three (3) months of general nursing experience;



        Demonstrates theoretical knowledge of the nursing process as it relates to the general medicine patient and the ability to apply this knowledge in a clinical setting;



        Theoretical knowledge of the care of the geriatric patient, and ability to apply this knowledge in a clinical setting;



        Demonstrates the ability to assess the patient's learning needs and ability to plan appropriate teaching;



        Demonstrates the ability to work effectively in a collaborative multidisciplinary approach to patient care;



        Demonstrates the ability to assess the patient's discharge needs and participates in the planning process;



        Demonstrates the ability to communicate effectively in an oral and written format with patients, public, colleagues and other health discipline;



        Demonstrates interpersonal and problem solving skills;



        Identifies a commitment to personal continuing education activities;



        Demonstrates an understanding and a willingness to participate in self-evaluation;



        Demonstrates an understanding of the application and relevance of the Quality Assurance Program and participates in unit activities;



        Must be eligible to work in Canada.








   Preferred Qualifications 




      A degree in Nursing.







   What you can expect from us 




      The Ottawa Hospital is committed to providing a healthy, safe, and inclusive work environment for everyone. We are driven by our purpose to provide each patient with the world-class care, exceptional service and compassion we would want for our loved ones.




       We offer an attractive and equitable compensation package including a comprehensive benefits package, a Defined Benefit Pension (DBP) plan, and insurance protection. We also offer discounts from choice providers on a variety of products and services. 




      The Ottawa Hospital provides various Health and Wellness resources as well as opportunities for personal and professional development opportunities from our in-house Learning and Leadership Development team to help align your goals with your career objectives.







   Interested? Apply today! 




      If you are passionate about what you do, motivated by improving the health of the community, excited by leading-edge medical technology, and as committed to excellence, quality and patient safety as we are, we would like to hear from you. Please submit an on-line application for the position you are interested in. We thank all those who apply but only those selected for further consideration will be contacted.
       The Ottawa Hospital is an equal opportunity employer. Upon request, accommodations due to a disability are available throughout the recruitment process.

Position Information





     Reporting to the Vice Chair (VC) of Research, the Manager, Research Services is responsible for a positive work culture, the development, implementation, and maintenance of work practices to permit the delivery of high-quality and efficient research coordination services while building excellence and capacity to respond to the research portfolio within the Department of Medicine (DoM). This includes managing a team, the administration and distribution of workload, communicating across teams, and performing quality control and assurance activities as required. The Manager develops processes and procedures, ensures fair and equitable access to resources, and identifies and addresses opportunities to improve processes and support and facilitate projects and communication to increase research productivity and impact. 






    Rotation/Shifts





     Days, 8 hour shifts. 






    Responsibilities






      Work with the VC of Research, the VC of Member Support, and Technical Solutions Office (TSO) to develop and maintain an online 'hub' for researchers to navigate the complexity of the researcher environment;
      Ensures equity in accessing Office services and resources;
      Manages the staff of the Research Office, prioritizes and delegates workload to meet multiple demands, ensuring deadlines are met; provides guidance/training/coaching to Research Office employees;
      Provide operational support to Vice-Chair of Research, including preparing and managing the annual Office budget;
      Monitors the Office¿s programs and service offerings and makes appropriate recommendations to capitalize on opportunities, mitigate risk, and resolve issues;
      Build and maintain productive and supportive relationships to facilitate research within DOM;
      Provide advice and guidance on funding opportunities, complex REB submissions, ethics proposals, publications, etc.;
      Manage compliance, limitations, and maintenance of the internal research output measurement system;
      Coordinate operational support for the Research Plus Program and the Director, Medical Education Research;
      Works to develop strategies to increase the visibility of DoM's research accomplishments and promote research events and activities.







    Basic Requirements








       Minimum of 7 years of experience in clinical research at an academic hospital is strongly preferred, including but not limited to clinical trial management, and academic-led studies;
       Familiarity with scientometric;
       Experience with research ethics guidelines, applications and REB requirements;
       Familiarity with concepts of The San Francisco Declaration on Research Assessment (DORA);
       Demonstrated relevant clinical research knowledge;
       A minimum of 5 years supervisory/management experience;
       Working knowledge of clinical research standards and regulations governing human research ethics;
       Ability to set priorities, work under pressure and meet deadlines with an attention to detail;
       Experience in leadership, mentoring, and creating positive working relationships, demonstrating tact and diplomacy;
       Experiencing with managing a budgets and metric reporting;
       Ability to handle highly sensitive and confidential information;
       Excellent interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills;
       Client service oriented, with the ability to work effectively in a highly diverse environment;
       Ability to exercise judgement and make decisions while working with minimal supervision;
       Proficiency in speaking and comprehending both English and French (Level B+) is an asset .








    Interested? Apply today!





     To apply for this exciting opportunity, please forward your resume and cover letter, quoting the corresponding position title, by email at domcareers@toh.ca
      IMPORTANT NOTICE: Support staff are employees of the University of Ottawa Medical Associates. The Ottawa Hospital is the paymaster of our employees. Although our employees have offices within the Ottawa Hospital, they are not employed by the Ottawa Hospital. The University of Ottawa Medical Associates is committed to the principle of equal opportunity in its employment practices and to providing an environment free from discrimination and harassment for all employees. The University of Ottawa Medical Associates will, upon request, provide accommodations in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act.

